details:
Case 177 is an imported case involving a 26 year-old male Singapore Citizen who had been in the US from 14 February to 24 February, UK from 28 February to 1 March, and France from 2 March to 7 March. He is warded in an isolation room at National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID).

He reported onset of symptoms on 9 March and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 10 March. He was conveyed by ambulance to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) and subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 11 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, he had mostly stayed at his home at Telok Blangah Street 31.
